The paper deals with a computer vision problem of selecting the best moment from a burst sequence of frames captured by a mobile camera. The proposed solution involves a deep neural network ranking model that learns a latent relative attribute space to capture subtle visual differences within the sequence. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training the model in an end-to-end fashion, which is a common approach in Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a deep neural network also suggests that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves exploring and evaluating different network design choices, which is a common approach in Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
